{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":2000,"text":"I want to start my talk today with two observations"},{"time":4000,"text":"about the human species."},{"time":6000,"text":"The first observation is something that you might think is quite obvious,"},{"time":9000,"text":"and that's that our species, Homo sapiens,"},{"time":11000,"text":"is actually really, really smart --"},{"time":13000,"text":"like, ridiculously smart --"},{"time":15000,"text":"like you're all doing things"},{"time":17000,"text":"that no other species on the planet does right now."},{"time":20000,"text":"And this is, of course,"},{"time":22000,"text":"not the first time you've probably recognized this."},{"time":24000,"text":"Of course, in addition to being smart, we're also an extremely vain species."},{"time":27000,"text":"So we like pointing out the fact that we're smart."},{"time":30000,"text":"You know, so I could turn to pretty much any sage"},{"time":32000,"text":"from Shakespeare to Stephen Colbert"},{"time":34000,"text":"to point out things like the fact that"},{"time":36000,"text":"we're noble in reason and infinite in faculties"},{"time":38000,"text":"and just kind of awesome-er than anything else on the planet"},{"time":40000,"text":"when it comes to all things cerebral."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43000,"text":"But of course, there's a second observation about the human species"},{"time":45000,"text":"that I want to focus on a little bit more,"},{"time":47000,"text":"and that's the fact that"},{"time":49000,"text":"even though we're actually really smart, sometimes uniquely smart,"},{"time":52000,"text":"we can also be incredibly, incredibly dumb"},{"time":55000,"text":"when it comes to some aspects of our decision making."},{"time":58000,"text":"Now I'm seeing lots of smirks out there."},{"time":60000,"text":"Don't worry, I'm not going to call anyone in particular out"},{"time":62000,"text":"on any aspects of your own mistakes."},{"time":64000,"text":"But of course, just in the last two years"},{"time":66000,"text":"we see these unprecedented examples of human ineptitude."},{"time":69000,"text":"And we've watched as the tools we uniquely make"},{"time":72000,"text":"to pull the resources out of our environment"},{"time":74000,"text":"kind of just blow up in our face."},{"time":76000,"text":"We've watched the financial markets that we uniquely create --"},{"time":78000,"text":"these markets that were supposed to be foolproof --"},{"time":81000,"text":"we've watched them kind of collapse before our eyes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":83000,"text":"But both of these two embarrassing examples, I think,"},{"time":85000,"text":"don't highlight what I think is most embarrassing"},{"time":88000,"text":"about the mistakes that humans make,"},{"time":90000,"text":"which is that we'd like to think that the mistakes we make"},{"time":93000,"text":"are really just the result of a couple bad apples"},{"time":95000,"text":"or a couple really sort of FAIL Blog-worthy decisions."},{"time":98000,"text":"But it turns out, what social scientists are actually learning"},{"time":101000,"text":"is that most of us, when put in certain contexts,"},{"time":104000,"text":"will actually make very specific mistakes."},{"time":107000,"text":"The errors we make are actually predictable."},{"time":109000,"text":"We make them again and again."},{"time":111000,"text":"And they're actually immune to lots of evidence."},{"time":113000,"text":"When we get negative feedback,"},{"time":115000,"text":"we still, the next time we're face with a certain context,"},{"time":118000,"text":"tend to make the same errors."},{"time":120000,"text":"And so this has been a real puzzle to me"},{"time":122000,"text":"as a sort of scholar of human nature."},{"time":124000,"text":"What I'm most curious about is,"},{"time":126000,"text":"how is a species that's as smart as we are"},{"time":129000,"text":"capable of such bad"},{"time":131000,"text":"and such consistent errors all the time?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":133000,"text":"You know, we're the smartest thing out there, why can't we figure this out?"},{"time":136000,"text":"In some sense, where do our mistakes really come from?"},{"time":139000,"text":"And having thought about this a little bit, I see a couple different possibilities."},{"time":142000,"text":"One possibility is, in some sense, it's not really our fault."},{"time":145000,"text":"Because we're a smart species,"},{"time":147000,"text":"we can actually create all kinds of environments"},{"time":149000,"text":"that are super, super complicated,"},{"time":151000,"text":"sometimes too complicated for us to even actually understand,"},{"time":154000,"text":"even though we've actually created them."},{"time":156000,"text":"We create financial markets that are super complex."},{"time":158000,"text":"We create mortgage terms that we can't actually deal with."},{"time":161000,"text":"And of course, if we are put in environments where we can't deal with it,"},{"time":164000,"text":"in some sense makes sense that we actually"},{"time":166000,"text":"might mess certain things up."},{"time":168000,"text":"If this was the case, we'd have a really easy solution"},{"time":170000,"text":"to the problem of human error."},{"time":172000,"text":"We'd actually just say, okay, let's figure out"},{"time":174000,"text":"the kinds of technologies we can't deal with,"},{"time":176000,"text":"the kinds of environments that are bad --"},{"time":178000,"text":"get rid of those, design things better,"},{"time":180000,"text":"and we should be the noble species"},{"time":182000,"text":"that we expect ourselves to be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":184000,"text":"But there's another possibility that I find a little bit more worrying,"},{"time":187000,"text":"which is, maybe it's not our environments that are messed up."},{"time":190000,"text":"Maybe it's actually us that's designed badly."},{"time":193000,"text":"This is a hint that I've gotten"},{"time":195000,"text":"from watching the ways that social scientists have learned about human errors."},{"time":198000,"text":"And what we see is that people tend to keep making errors"},{"time":201000,"text":"exactly the same way, over and over again."},{"time":204000,"text":"It feels like we might almost just be built"},{"time":206000,"text":"to make errors in certain ways."},{"time":208000,"text":"This is a possibility that I worry a little bit more about,"},{"time":211000,"text":"because, if it's us that's messed up,"},{"time":213000,"text":"it's not actually clear how we go about dealing with it."},{"time":215000,"text":"We might just have to accept the fact that we're error prone"},{"time":218000,"text":"and try to design things around it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":220000,"text":"So this is the question my students and I wanted to get at."},{"time":223000,"text":"How can we tell the difference between possibility one and possibility two?"},{"time":226000,"text":"What we need is a population"},{"time":228000,"text":"that's basically smart, can make lots of decisions,"},{"time":230000,"text":"but doesn't have access to any of the systems we have,"},{"time":232000,"text":"any of the things that might mess us up --"},{"time":234000,"text":"no human technology, human culture,"},{"time":236000,"text":"maybe even not human language."},{"time":238000,"text":"And so this is why we turned to these guys here."},{"time":240000,"text":"These are one of the guys I work with. This is a brown capuchin monkey."},{"time":243000,"text":"These guys are New World primates,"},{"time":245000,"text":"which means they broke off from the human branch"},{"time":247000,"text":"about 35 million years ago."},{"time":249000,"text":"This means that your great, great, great great, great, great --"},{"time":251000,"text":"with about five million \"greats\" in there --"},{"time":253000,"text":"grandmother was probably the same great, great, great, great"},{"time":255000,"text":"grandmother with five million \"greats\" in there"},{"time":257000,"text":"as Holly up here."},{"time":259000,"text":"You know, so you can take comfort in the fact that this guy up here is a really really distant,"},{"time":262000,"text":"but albeit evolutionary, relative."},{"time":264000,"text":"The good news about Holly though is that"},{"time":266000,"text":"she doesn't actually have the same kinds of technologies we do."},{"time":269000,"text":"You know, she's a smart, very cut creature, a primate as well,"},{"time":272000,"text":"but she lacks all the stuff we think might be messing us up."},{"time":274000,"text":"So she's the perfect test case."}]},{"cues":[{"time":276000,"text":"What if we put Holly into the same context as humans?"},{"time":279000,"text":"Does she make the same mistakes as us?"},{"time":281000,"text":"Does she not learn from them? And so on."},{"time":283000,"text":"And so this is the kind of thing we decided to do."},{"time":285000,"text":"My students and I got very excited about this a few years ago."},{"time":287000,"text":"We said, all right, let's, you know, throw so problems at Holly,"},{"time":289000,"text":"see if she messes these things up."},{"time":291000,"text":"First problem is just, well, where should we start?"},{"time":294000,"text":"Because, you know, it's great for us, but bad for humans."},{"time":296000,"text":"We make a lot of mistakes in a lot of different contexts."},{"time":298000,"text":"You know, where are we actually going to start with this?"},{"time":300000,"text":"And because we started this work around the time of the financial collapse,"},{"time":303000,"text":"around the time when foreclosures were hitting the news,"},{"time":305000,"text":"we said, hhmm, maybe we should"},{"time":307000,"text":"actually start in the financial domain."},{"time":309000,"text":"Maybe we should look at monkey's economic decisions"},{"time":312000,"text":"and try to see if they do the same kinds of dumb things that we do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":315000,"text":"Of course, that's when we hit a sort second problem --"},{"time":317000,"text":"a little bit more methodological --"},{"time":319000,"text":"which is that, maybe you guys don't know,"},{"time":321000,"text":"but monkeys don't actually use money. I know, you haven't met them."},{"time":324000,"text":"But this is why, you know, they're not in the queue behind you"},{"time":326000,"text":"at the grocery store or the ATM -- you know, they don't do this stuff."},{"time":329000,"text":"So now we faced, you know, a little bit of a problem here."},{"time":332000,"text":"How are we actually going to ask monkeys about money"},{"time":334000,"text":"if they don't actually use it?"},{"time":336000,"text":"So we said, well, maybe we should just, actually just suck it up"},{"time":338000,"text":"and teach monkeys how to use money."},{"time":340000,"text":"So that's just what we did."},{"time":342000,"text":"What you're looking at over here is actually the first unit that I know of"},{"time":345000,"text":"of non-human currency."},{"time":347000,"text":"We weren't very creative at the time we started these studies,"},{"time":349000,"text":"so we just called it a token."},{"time":351000,"text":"But this is the unit of currency that we've taught our monkeys at Yale"},{"time":354000,"text":"to actually use with humans,"},{"time":356000,"text":"to actually buy different pieces of food."},{"time":359000,"text":"It doesn't look like much -- in fact, it isn't like much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361000,"text":"Like most of our money, it's just a piece of metal."},{"time":363000,"text":"As those of you who've taken currencies home from your trip know,"},{"time":366000,"text":"once you get home, it's actually pretty useless."},{"time":368000,"text":"It was useless to the monkeys at first"},{"time":370000,"text":"before they realized what they could do with it."},{"time":372000,"text":"When we first gave it to them in their enclosures,"},{"time":374000,"text":"they actually kind of picked them up, looked at them."},{"time":376000,"text":"They were these kind of weird things."},{"time":378000,"text":"But very quickly, the monkeys realized"},{"time":380000,"text":"that they could actually hand these tokens over"},{"time":382000,"text":"to different humans in the lab for some food."},{"time":385000,"text":"And so you see one of our monkeys, Mayday, up here doing this."},{"time":387000,"text":"This is A and B are kind of the points where she's sort of a little bit"},{"time":390000,"text":"curious about these things -- doesn't know."},{"time":392000,"text":"There's this waiting hand from a human experimenter,"},{"time":394000,"text":"and Mayday quickly figures out, apparently the human wants this."},{"time":397000,"text":"Hands it over, and then gets some food."},{"time":399000,"text":"It turns out not just Mayday, all of our monkeys get good"},{"time":401000,"text":"at trading tokens with human salesman."},{"time":403000,"text":"So here's just a quick video of what this looks like."},{"time":405000,"text":"Here's Mayday. She's going to be trading a token for some food"},{"time":408000,"text":"and waiting happily and getting her food."},{"time":411000,"text":"Here's Felix, I think. He's our alpha male; he's a kind of big guy."},{"time":413000,"text":"But he too waits patiently, gets his food and goes on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416000,"text":"So the monkeys get really good at this."},{"time":418000,"text":"They're surprisingly good at this with very little training."},{"time":421000,"text":"We just allowed them to pick this up on their own."},{"time":423000,"text":"The question is: is this anything like human money?"},{"time":425000,"text":"Is this a market at all,"},{"time":427000,"text":"or did we just do a weird psychologist's trick"},{"time":429000,"text":"by getting monkeys to do something,"},{"time":431000,"text":"looking smart, but not really being smart."},{"time":433000,"text":"And so we said, well, what would the monkeys spontaneously do"},{"time":436000,"text":"if this was really their currency, if they were really using it like money?"},{"time":439000,"text":"Well, you might actually imagine them"},{"time":441000,"text":"to do all the kinds of smart things"},{"time":443000,"text":"that humans do when they start exchanging money with each other."},{"time":446000,"text":"You might have them start paying attention to price,"},{"time":449000,"text":"paying attention to how much they buy --"},{"time":451000,"text":"sort of keeping track of their monkey token, as it were."},{"time":454000,"text":"Do the monkeys do anything like this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":456000,"text":"And so our monkey marketplace was born."},{"time":459000,"text":"The way this works is that"},{"time":461000,"text":"our monkeys normally live in a kind of big zoo social enclosure."},{"time":464000,"text":"When they get a hankering for some treats,"},{"time":466000,"text":"we actually allowed them a way out"},{"time":468000,"text":"into a little smaller enclosure where they could enter the market."},{"time":470000,"text":"Upon entering the market --"},{"time":472000,"text":"it was actually a much more fun market for the monkeys than most human markets"},{"time":474000,"text":"because, as the monkeys entered the door of the market,"},{"time":477000,"text":"a human would give them a big wallet full of tokens"},{"time":479000,"text":"so they could actually trade the tokens"},{"time":481000,"text":"with one of these two guys here --"},{"time":483000,"text":"two different possible human salesmen"},{"time":485000,"text":"that they could actually buy stuff from."},{"time":487000,"text":"The salesmen were students from my lab."},{"time":489000,"text":"They dressed differently; they were different people."},{"time":491000,"text":"And over time, they did basically the same thing"},{"time":494000,"text":"so the monkeys could learn, you know,"},{"time":496000,"text":"who sold what at what price -- you know, who was reliable, who wasn't, and so on."},{"time":499000,"text":"And you can see that each of the experimenters"},{"time":501000,"text":"is actually holding up a little, yellow food dish."},{"time":504000,"text":"and that's what the monkey can for a single token."},{"time":506000,"text":"So everything costs one token,"},{"time":508000,"text":"but as you can see, sometimes tokens buy more than others,"},{"time":510000,"text":"sometimes more grapes than others."}]},{"cues":[{"time":512000,"text":"So I'll show you a quick video of what this marketplace actually looks like."},{"time":515000,"text":"Here's a monkey-eye-view. Monkeys are shorter, so it's a little short."},{"time":518000,"text":"But here's Honey."},{"time":520000,"text":"She's waiting for the market to open a little impatiently."},{"time":522000,"text":"All of a sudden the market opens. Here's her choice: one grapes or two grapes."},{"time":525000,"text":"You can see Honey, very good market economist,"},{"time":527000,"text":"goes with the guy who gives more."},{"time":530000,"text":"She could teach our financial advisers a few things or two."},{"time":532000,"text":"So not just Honey,"},{"time":534000,"text":"most of the monkeys went with guys who had more."},{"time":537000,"text":"Most of the monkeys went with guys who had better food."},{"time":539000,"text":"When we introduced sales, we saw the monkeys paid attention to that."},{"time":542000,"text":"They really cared about their monkey token dollar."},{"time":545000,"text":"The more surprising thing was that when we collaborated with economists"},{"time":548000,"text":"to actually look at the monkeys' data using economic tools,"},{"time":551000,"text":"they basically matched, not just qualitatively,"},{"time":554000,"text":"but quantitatively with what we saw"},{"time":556000,"text":"humans doing in a real market."},{"time":558000,"text":"So much so that, if you saw the monkeys' numbers,"},{"time":560000,"text":"you couldn't tell whether they came from a monkey or a human in the same market."}]},{"cues":[{"time":563000,"text":"And what we'd really thought we'd done"},{"time":565000,"text":"is like we'd actually introduced something"},{"time":567000,"text":"that, at least for the monkeys and us,"},{"time":569000,"text":"works like a real financial currency."},{"time":571000,"text":"Question is: do the monkeys start messing up in the same ways we do?"},{"time":574000,"text":"Well, we already saw anecdotally a couple of signs that they might."},{"time":577000,"text":"One thing we never saw in the monkey marketplace"},{"time":579000,"text":"was any evidence of saving --"},{"time":581000,"text":"you know, just like our own species."},{"time":583000,"text":"The monkeys entered the market, spent their entire budget"},{"time":585000,"text":"and then went back to everyone else."},{"time":587000,"text":"The other thing we also spontaneously saw,"},{"time":589000,"text":"embarrassingly enough,"},{"time":591000,"text":"is spontaneous evidence of larceny."},{"time":593000,"text":"The monkeys would rip-off the tokens at every available opportunity --"},{"time":596000,"text":"from each other, often from us --"},{"time":598000,"text":"you know, things we didn't necessarily think we were introducing,"},{"time":600000,"text":"but things we spontaneously saw."}]},{"cues":[{"time":602000,"text":"So we said, this looks bad."},{"time":604000,"text":"Can we actually see if the monkeys"},{"time":606000,"text":"are doing exactly the same dumb things as humans do?"},{"time":609000,"text":"One possibility is just kind of let"},{"time":611000,"text":"the monkey financial system play out,"},{"time":613000,"text":"you know, see if they start calling us for bailouts in a few years."},{"time":615000,"text":"We were a little impatient so we wanted"},{"time":617000,"text":"to sort of speed things up a bit."},{"time":619000,"text":"So we said, let's actually give the monkeys"},{"time":621000,"text":"the same kinds of problems"},{"time":623000,"text":"that humans tend to get wrong"},{"time":625000,"text":"in certain kinds of economic challenges,"},{"time":627000,"text":"or certain kinds of economic experiments."},{"time":629000,"text":"And so, since the best way to see how people go wrong"},{"time":632000,"text":"is to actually do it yourself,"},{"time":634000,"text":"I'm going to give you guys a quick experiment"},{"time":636000,"text":"to sort of watch your own financial intuitions in action."}]},{"cues":[{"time":638000,"text":"So imagine that right now"},{"time":640000,"text":"I handed each and every one of you"},{"time":642000,"text":"a thousand U.S. dollars -- so 10 crisp hundred dollar bills."},{"time":645000,"text":"Take these, put it in your wallet"},{"time":647000,"text":"and spend a second thinking about what you're going to do with it."},{"time":649000,"text":"Because it's yours now; you can buy whatever you want."},{"time":651000,"text":"Donate it, take it, and so on."},{"time":653000,"text":"Sounds great, but you get one more choice to earn a little bit more money."},{"time":656000,"text":"And here's your choice: you can either be risky,"},{"time":659000,"text":"in which case I'm going to flip one of these monkey tokens."},{"time":661000,"text":"If it comes up heads, you're going to get a thousand dollars more."},{"time":663000,"text":"If it comes up tails, you get nothing."},{"time":665000,"text":"So it's a chance to get more, but it's pretty risky."},{"time":668000,"text":"Your other option is a bit safe. Your just going to get some money for sure."},{"time":671000,"text":"I'm just going to give you 500 bucks."},{"time":673000,"text":"You can stick it in your wallet and use it immediately."},{"time":676000,"text":"So see what your intuition is here."},{"time":678000,"text":"Most people actually go with the play-it-safe option."},{"time":681000,"text":"Most people say, why should I be risky when I can get 1,500 dollars for sure?"},{"time":684000,"text":"This seems like a good bet. I'm going to go with that."},{"time":686000,"text":"You might say, eh, that's not really irrational."},{"time":688000,"text":"People are a little risk-averse. So what?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":690000,"text":"Well, the \"so what?\" comes when start thinking"},{"time":692000,"text":"about the same problem"},{"time":694000,"text":"set up just a little bit differently."},{"time":696000,"text":"So now imagine that I give each and every one of you"},{"time":698000,"text":"2,000 dollars -- 20 crisp hundred dollar bills."},{"time":701000,"text":"Now you can buy double to stuff you were going to get before."},{"time":703000,"text":"Think about how you'd feel sticking it in your wallet."},{"time":705000,"text":"And now imagine that I have you make another choice"},{"time":707000,"text":"But this time, it's a little bit worse."},{"time":709000,"text":"Now, you're going to be deciding how you're going to lose money,"},{"time":712000,"text":"but you're going to get the same choice."},{"time":714000,"text":"You can either take a risky loss --"},{"time":716000,"text":"so I'll flip a coin. If it comes up heads, you're going to actually lose a lot."},{"time":719000,"text":"If it comes up tails, you lose nothing, you're fine, get to keep the whole thing --"},{"time":722000,"text":"or you could play it safe, which means you have to reach back into your wallet"},{"time":725000,"text":"and give me five of those $100 bills, for certain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":728000,"text":"And I'm seeing a lot of furrowed brows out there."},{"time":731000,"text":"So maybe you're having the same intuitions"},{"time":733000,"text":"as the subjects that were actually tested in this,"},{"time":735000,"text":"which is when presented with these options,"},{"time":737000,"text":"people don't choose to play it safe."},{"time":739000,"text":"They actually tend to go a little risky."},{"time":741000,"text":"The reason this is irrational is that we've given people in both situations"},{"time":744000,"text":"the same choice."},{"time":746000,"text":"It's a 50/50 shot of a thousand or 2,000,"},{"time":749000,"text":"or just 1,500 dollars with certainty."},{"time":751000,"text":"But people's intuitions about how much risk to take"},{"time":754000,"text":"varies depending on where they started with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":756000,"text":"So what's going on?"},{"time":758000,"text":"Well, it turns out that this seems to be the result"},{"time":760000,"text":"of at least two biases that we have at the psychological level."},{"time":763000,"text":"One is that we have a really hard time thinking in absolute terms."},{"time":766000,"text":"You really have to do work to figure out,"},{"time":768000,"text":"well, one option's a thousand, 2,000;"},{"time":770000,"text":"one is 1,500."},{"time":772000,"text":"Instead, we find it very easy to think in very relative terms"},{"time":775000,"text":"as options change from one time to another."},{"time":778000,"text":"So we think of things as, \"Oh, I'm going to get more,\" or \"Oh, I'm going to get less.\""},{"time":781000,"text":"This is all well and good, except that"},{"time":783000,"text":"changes in different directions"},{"time":785000,"text":"actually effect whether or not we think"},{"time":787000,"text":"options are good or not."},{"time":789000,"text":"And this leads to the second bias,"},{"time":791000,"text":"which economists have called loss aversion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":793000,"text":"The idea is that we really hate it when things go into the red."},{"time":796000,"text":"We really hate it when we have to lose out on some money."},{"time":798000,"text":"And this means that sometimes we'll actually"},{"time":800000,"text":"switch our preferences to avoid this."},{"time":802000,"text":"What you saw in that last scenario is that"},{"time":804000,"text":"subjects get risky"},{"time":806000,"text":"because they want the small shot that there won't be any loss."},{"time":809000,"text":"That means when we're in a risk mindset --"},{"time":811000,"text":"excuse me, when we're in a loss mindset,"},{"time":813000,"text":"we actually become more risky,"},{"time":815000,"text":"which can actually be really worrying."},{"time":817000,"text":"These kinds of things play out in lots of bad ways in humans."},{"time":820000,"text":"They're why stock investors hold onto losing stocks longer --"},{"time":823000,"text":"because they're evaluating them in relative terms."},{"time":825000,"text":"They're why people in the housing market refused to sell their house --"},{"time":827000,"text":"because they don't want to sell at a loss."}]},{"cues":[{"time":829000,"text":"The question we were interested in"},{"time":831000,"text":"is whether the monkeys show the same biases."},{"time":833000,"text":"If we set up those same scenarios in our little monkey market,"},{"time":836000,"text":"would they do the same thing as people?"},{"time":838000,"text":"And so this is what we did, we gave the monkeys choices"},{"time":840000,"text":"between guys who were safe -- they did the same thing every time --"},{"time":843000,"text":"or guys who were risky --"},{"time":845000,"text":"they did things differently half the time."},{"time":847000,"text":"And then we gave them options that were bonuses --"},{"time":849000,"text":"like you guys did in the first scenario --"},{"time":851000,"text":"so they actually have a chance more,"},{"time":853000,"text":"or pieces where they were experiencing losses --"},{"time":856000,"text":"they actually thought they were going to get more than they really got."}]},{"cues":[{"time":858000,"text":"And so this is what this looks like."},{"time":860000,"text":"We introduced the monkeys to two new monkey salesmen."},{"time":862000,"text":"The guy on the left and right both start with one piece of grape,"},{"time":864000,"text":"so it looks pretty good."},{"time":866000,"text":"But they're going to give the monkeys bonuses."},{"time":868000,"text":"The guy on the left is a safe bonus."},{"time":870000,"text":"All the time, he adds one, to give the monkeys two."},{"time":873000,"text":"The guy on the right is actually a risky bonus."},{"time":875000,"text":"Sometimes the monkeys get no bonus -- so this is a bonus of zero."},{"time":878000,"text":"Sometimes the monkeys get two extra."},{"time":881000,"text":"For a big bonus, now they get three."},{"time":883000,"text":"But this is the same choice you guys just faced."},{"time":885000,"text":"Do the monkeys actually want to play it safe"},{"time":888000,"text":"and then go with the guy who's going to do the same thing on every trial,"},{"time":890000,"text":"or do they want to be risky"},{"time":892000,"text":"and try to get a risky, but big, bonus,"},{"time":894000,"text":"but risk the possibility of getting no bonus."},{"time":896000,"text":"People here played it safe."},{"time":898000,"text":"Turns out, the monkeys play it safe too."},{"time":900000,"text":"Qualitatively and quantitatively,"},{"time":902000,"text":"they choose exactly the same way as people,"},{"time":904000,"text":"when tested in the same thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":906000,"text":"You might say, well, maybe the monkeys just don't like risk."},{"time":908000,"text":"Maybe we should see how they do with losses."},{"time":910000,"text":"And so we ran a second version of this."},{"time":912000,"text":"Now, the monkeys meet two guys"},{"time":914000,"text":"who aren't giving them bonuses;"},{"time":916000,"text":"they're actually giving them less than they expect."},{"time":918000,"text":"So they look like they're starting out with a big amount."},{"time":920000,"text":"These are three grapes; the monkey's really psyched for this."},{"time":922000,"text":"But now they learn these guys are going to give them less than they expect."},{"time":925000,"text":"They guy on the left is a safe loss."},{"time":927000,"text":"Every single time, he's going to take one of these away"},{"time":930000,"text":"and give the monkeys just two."},{"time":932000,"text":"the guy on the right is the risky loss."},{"time":934000,"text":"Sometimes he gives no loss, so the monkeys are really psyched,"},{"time":937000,"text":"but sometimes he actually gives a big loss,"},{"time":939000,"text":"taking away two to give the monkeys only one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":941000,"text":"And so what do the monkeys do?"},{"time":943000,"text":"Again, same choice; they can play it safe"},{"time":945000,"text":"for always getting two grapes every single time,"},{"time":948000,"text":"or they can take a risky bet and choose between one and three."},{"time":951000,"text":"The remarkable thing to us is that, when you give monkeys this choice,"},{"time":954000,"text":"they do the same irrational thing that people do."},{"time":956000,"text":"They actually become more risky"},{"time":958000,"text":"depending on how the experimenters started."},{"time":961000,"text":"This is crazy because it suggests that the monkeys too"},{"time":963000,"text":"are evaluating things in relative terms"},{"time":965000,"text":"and actually treating losses differently than they treat gains."}]},{"cues":[{"time":968000,"text":"So what does all of this mean?"},{"time":970000,"text":"Well, what we've shown is that, first of all,"},{"time":972000,"text":"we can actually give the monkeys a financial currency,"},{"time":974000,"text":"and they do very similar things with it."},{"time":976000,"text":"They do some of the smart things we do,"},{"time":978000,"text":"some of the kind of not so nice things we do,"},{"time":980000,"text":"like steal it and so on."},{"time":982000,"text":"But they also do some of the irrational things we do."},{"time":984000,"text":"They systematically get things wrong"},{"time":986000,"text":"and in the same ways that we do."},{"time":988000,"text":"This is the first take-home message of the Talk,"},{"time":990000,"text":"which is that if you saw the beginning of this and you thought,"},{"time":992000,"text":"oh, I'm totally going to go home and hire a capuchin monkey financial adviser."},{"time":994000,"text":"They're way cuter than the one at ... you know --"},{"time":996000,"text":"Don't do that; they're probably going to be just as dumb"},{"time":998000,"text":"as the human one you already have."},{"time":1001000,"text":"So, you know, a little bad -- Sorry, sorry, sorry."},{"time":1003000,"text":"A little bad for monkey investors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1005000,"text":"But of course, you know, the reason you're laughing is bad for humans too."},{"time":1008000,"text":"Because we've answered the question we started out with."},{"time":1011000,"text":"We wanted to know where these kinds of errors came from."},{"time":1013000,"text":"And we started with the hope that maybe we can"},{"time":1015000,"text":"sort of tweak our financial institutions,"},{"time":1017000,"text":"tweak our technologies to make ourselves better."},{"time":1020000,"text":"But what we've learn is that these biases might be a deeper part of us than that."},{"time":1023000,"text":"In fact, they might be due to the very nature"},{"time":1025000,"text":"of our evolutionary history."},{"time":1027000,"text":"You know, maybe it's not just humans"},{"time":1029000,"text":"at the right side of this chain that's duncey."},{"time":1031000,"text":"Maybe it's sort of duncey all the way back."},{"time":1033000,"text":"And this, if we believe the capuchin monkey results,"},{"time":1036000,"text":"means that these duncey strategies"},{"time":1038000,"text":"might be 35 million years old."},{"time":1040000,"text":"That's a long time for a strategy"},{"time":1042000,"text":"to potentially get changed around -- really, really old."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1045000,"text":"What do we know about other old strategies like this?"},{"time":1047000,"text":"Well, one thing we know is that they tend to be really hard to overcome."},{"time":1050000,"text":"You know, think of our evolutionary predilection"},{"time":1052000,"text":"for eating sweet things, fatty things like cheesecake."},{"time":1055000,"text":"You can't just shut that off."},{"time":1057000,"text":"You can't just look at the dessert cart as say, \"No, no, no. That looks disgusting to me.\""},{"time":1060000,"text":"We're just built differently."},{"time":1062000,"text":"We're going to perceive it as a good thing to go after."},{"time":1064000,"text":"My guess is that the same thing is going to be true"},{"time":1066000,"text":"when humans are perceiving"},{"time":1068000,"text":"different financial decisions."},{"time":1070000,"text":"When you're watching your stocks plummet into the red,"},{"time":1072000,"text":"when you're watching your house price go down,"},{"time":1074000,"text":"you're not going to be able to see that"},{"time":1076000,"text":"in anything but old evolutionary terms."},{"time":1078000,"text":"This means that the biases"},{"time":1080000,"text":"that lead investors to do badly,"},{"time":1082000,"text":"that lead to the foreclosure crisis"},{"time":1084000,"text":"are going to be really hard to overcome."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1086000,"text":"So that's the bad news. The question is: is there any good news?"},{"time":1088000,"text":"I'm supposed to be up here telling you the good news."},{"time":1090000,"text":"Well, the good news, I think,"},{"time":1092000,"text":"is what I started with at the beginning of the Talk,"},{"time":1094000,"text":"which is that humans are not only smart;"},{"time":1096000,"text":"we're really inspirationally smart"},{"time":1098000,"text":"to the rest of the animals in the biological kingdom."},{"time":1101000,"text":"We're so good at overcoming our biological limitations --"},{"time":1104000,"text":"you know, I flew over here in an airplane."},{"time":1106000,"text":"I didn't have to try to flap my wings."},{"time":1108000,"text":"I'm wearing contact lenses now so that I can see all of you."},{"time":1111000,"text":"I don't have to rely on my own near-sightedness."},{"time":1114000,"text":"We actually have all of these cases"},{"time":1116000,"text":"where we overcome our biological limitations"},{"time":1119000,"text":"through technology and other means, seemingly pretty easily."},{"time":1122000,"text":"But we have to recognize that we have those limitations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1125000,"text":"And here's the rub."},{"time":1127000,"text":"It was Camus who once said that, \"Man is the only species"},{"time":1129000,"text":"who refuses to be what he really is.\""},{"time":1132000,"text":"But the irony is that"},{"time":1134000,"text":"it might only be in recognizing our limitations"},{"time":1136000,"text":"that we can really actually overcome them."},{"time":1138000,"text":"The hope is that you all will think about your limitations,"},{"time":1141000,"text":"not necessarily as unovercomable,"},{"time":1144000,"text":"but to recognize them, accept them"},{"time":1146000,"text":"and then use the world of design to actually figure them out."},{"time":1149000,"text":"That might be the only way that we will really be able"},{"time":1152000,"text":"to achieve our own human potential"},{"time":1154000,"text":"and really be the noble species we hope to all be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1157000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1159000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}